Here’s a structured daily routine you can follow using the Trancy Vocabulary page to steadily build your word bank:

Step–by–Step Routine

🌅 Morning (10–15 min)

Pick a category that matches your level (e.g., CEFR B1–B2).

Save 5 new words into your list.

Quickly review their meanings and example sentences.

🕛 Midday (10 min)

Revisit the saved words.

Try to use each in a short sentence or note.

Add any new words you encounter while browsing or watching content (via the extension).

🌆 Evening (15–20 min)

Practice with the “Review” or “Mastered” sections.

Aim to move at least 2–3 words into “mastered.”

If you’re preparing for a test (IELTS, TOEFL, etc.), mix in words from that category.

🌙 End of Day Reflection (5 min)

Write a short paragraph using at least 3 of the day’s words.

Check if they feel natural in context.

Mark progress in the “All Mastered” section.

Weekly Goal

Save 35–50 new words (≈5–7 per day).

Move at least 15–20 words into “mastered.”

Rotate categories weekly (general CEFR → test prep → specialized sets).

This way, you’ll build vocabulary steadily without overload, and the “mastered” list will grow consistently.

7-Day Themed Vocabulary Plan

Day 1: Travel & Transportation

Words related to airports, hotels, directions, and transport.

Practice by describing a trip or planning a journey.

Quiz: Multiple choice questions on airport and hotel vocabulary; fill-in-the-blank sentences.

Example Dialogue:

Guest: "Hello, I have a reservation under the name Smith."

Receptionist: "Welcome, Mr. Smith. Your room is ready. Would you like help with your luggage?"

Multimedia Links:

Video: "Top 10 Airport Tips for Travelers" (YouTube) - Link

Podcast: "Travel Tales: Airport Stories" (Spotify) - Link

Specific Quiz Template:

Question 1: What is the place called where planes take off and land?

a) Bus station

b) Airport

c) Train station

Question 2: Fill in the blank: "I have a reservation under the name ___."

